            "questionText": "A car with a mass of $!$1200\\ \\text{kg}$!$ is traveling at $!$72\\ \\text{km/h}$!$. Upon impact with a rigid barrier, its crumple zones deform, absorbing the car's kinetic energy and bringing it to a complete stop over a distance of $!$0.8\\ \\text{m}$!$. Calculate the average force in Newtons exerted on the car by the crumple zones during the impact.",
